<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-10-03T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-10-03T05:00:00-05:00" n="557" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.105/30: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-10-03T18:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">October 3,
                                        1923—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 3—10:55
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>329. My 289, August 21, 10 a.m. Japanese Minister informed me this
                            afternoon that although his Government had objections to committee’s
                            plan yet in a spirit of accommodation they would not present them but
                            would approve it.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>